Cut to a row of dour Communists in ill-fitting gray suits announcingGorbachev's illness and a palace coup. The camera zooms in on the impassive

faces of the two men last seen in Gorbachev's office.; What is going on here?
But then, this week's events in the Soviet Union have all the makings of a spy thriller.; Kremlinologists who dabble in conspiracy theories are working overtime, though they insist that their darkest imaginings be clearly labeled "pure speculation."
; "Once you have a palace coup, the possibilities are endless," said Robert Conquest, a senior research fellow at the Hoover Institution.
; For all we know, Conquest joked, Gorbachev could be injected with drugs to change his personality or KGB scientists could produce a body-double to impersonate him.; "His friends would know, but would you or I?"
